Revision history for telegram-claude

0.02 2026-06-11
  - DD-384: fixed the managed verbose-trace progress callback. editMessageText
    returns 400 ("message is not modified") on unchanged text, which disabled
    the whole in-chat trace; the reporter now skips the no-op edit when the
    accumulated text is unchanged. Surfaced live in the noVNC E2E.
  - DD-385: fixed live-pane discovery. tmux rewrites a literal tab in a `-F`
    format to an underscore, so `tmux_pane_rows` split on `\t` collapsed every
    pane into one field and dropped it, breaking discovery of the live
    `claude --resume` TUI (and thus live-TUI injection / TUI->Telegram
    mirroring). Switched the tmux format/split to a pipe separator tmux
    preserves. Verified live against the real interactive Claude TUI.

0.01 2026-06-11
  - Initial release of the telegram-claude skill, replicating the
    telegram-codex Telegram bridge runtime but driving the Claude Code CLI
    (`claude`) instead of the Codex CLI.
  - Collector-owned Telegram polling through one DD collector per workspace
    session, with single-owner getUpdates per bot token and token-scoped shared
    poll roots under `~/.telegram-claude/.shared/<sha1(bot-token)>/`.
  - Managed replies resume the saved Claude session with
    `claude -p --resume <session-id> --output-format stream-json --verbose
    --dangerously-skip-permissions` and stream real Claude stream-json events
    (system/init, assistant text and tool_use, user tool_result, result) into
    one in-place Telegram verbose trace.
  - Live tmux session sharing targets `claude --resume <session-id>` processes
    and the shared transcript is the Claude Code JSONL at
    `~/.claude/projects/<encoded-cwd>/<session-id>.jsonl`.
  - Pairing security: first unpaired Telegram message gets one local
    `d2 telegram-claude.pair <hexcode>` challenge; only the paired chat can drive
    the session afterward.
  - Inbound media downloaded into the session runtime; downloaded photos and
    image documents are referenced by local path in the prompt so the Claude
    Read tool can open them.
  - `dashboard telegram-claude.start --version` proxies the real
    `claude --version` output without collector side effects.
  - Docker noVNC E2E lab installs the Claude Code CLI
    (`@anthropic-ai/claude-code`).
